Job Title
Field Service Engineer Ultrasound
Job Description


In this role, you have the opportunity to

support Philips Ultrasound imaging systems in Wallonia and Luxembourg. You will take on the opportunity to build customer relationships through your effective use of technical knowledge to install, service, and maintain customer sites. You will be responsible for the different systems in the Ultrasound portfolio. These are used all over the hospital (radiology, cardiology, gynecology, vascular surgery, etc), but also in private practices. Learn more about our solutions here.

You are responsible for
Assisting in service repair, preventative maintenance, field change orders / installations;
Identifying and resolving customer issues, providing the customer with the appropriate communication and involving appropriate Service and Sales Personnel;
Operating under required knowledge of regulatory requirement (Federal and State Radiation performance standards, registration, Quality Systems Regulations, EPA regulations and OSHA regulations;
Defining problems: Collecting data, establishing facts and drawing valid conclusions. You have the ability to interpret an extensive variety of technical instructions and deal with abstract and concrete variables.
You are a part of

working as part of our Global Sales and Service organization, you will benefit from the team’s growing breadth and depth of healthcare products and services portfolio, and challenged to drive our best-in-class reputation through top customer experience ratings.

To succeed in this role, you should have the following skills and experience
Experience in the field service environment;
Experience in IT and connectivity is a strong asset;
Fluent in French and English (knowledge of Dutch is preferred);
Demonstrated repair and troubleshooting skills;
Ability to communicate effectively, share knowledge and cooperate in a team environment to achieve assigned goals and objectives. Able to perform in a leadership role in some circumstances. Proactively complete assignments;
Must possess a valid driver’s license;
Travel up to 50% to the customer site, zone office or identified meeting locations.
