Active contribution regarding deployment of new techniques, improvements and the architecture;
Helping PostNL improve and innovate on all our C# application stacks;
Supporting your peers and participating as a team member.

Onze ambitie

We want to be the favorite logistics company by delivering special moments every day. Our employees and customers are key. We are always looking to improve ourselves and for ways to differentiate with our IT capabilities. As Senior C# Engineer you are an essential linking pin in our transition to self-engineering. To help achieve this we will design and build (cloud-native) our own logistic business processes so that from an IT perspective we add enormous value to the business consequently our customers.

Wat breng jij mee?

At least 5 years software development experience as C# Developer, Programmer or Engineer;
Experience in analyzing business processes, designing and building data-driven software solutions;
Familiar with SQL and setting up and maintaining Relational Databases;
Software development experience using AWS cloud services, such as Lambda, ECS, S3, or equivalent;
Build-Test-Deploy automation experience: CI/CD pipelines;
Enjoys working according to Agile/Scrum principles;
Currently resident in the Netherlands and if required, in possession of the necessary work permits;
Dutch language proficiency (at least B1 level) or commitment to learn;
Available for at least 32 business hours per week and at least 3 days working at the PostNL office in the Hague.
By being self-starting and self-organizing and taking ownership your ideas become reality; You build it, you own it, you run it. Actively thinking about possible innovations whilst taking into account the most optimal use and application of the technical aspects.

Wat bezorgen we jou?

Competitive salary based on experience and the talent you bring to the table. between € 4.264 and max €6.201 (salary scale 11/12) based on 37 hours per week and in accordance with the PostNL Collective Labor Agreement;
Part- or fulltime position 32 till 37 hours with view to permanent contract;
Annual 8% holiday pay and 25 vacation days by fulltime contract;
A range of secondary benefits including collective Health insurance and attractive Pension scheme via our own Pension fund;
Professional growth opportunities, for example diversification to other languages, platforms or in-depth development of your specialism;
Room for personal development through education and training;
Office location: Easy Public Transport commute to our PostNL office in the Hague;
Engineering laptop, mobile phone and compensation towards your travel costs.
Furthermore, this role provides you with the opportunity to work in a dynamic, flexible and innovative environment. You will work in close collaboration with various platforms within PostNL so that besides developing you have an arena to create new ideas and innovations. You are an important member of a team that has a great impact on our digital transformation. Continuous improvement, innovation and deployment of the latest (cloud) techniques are vital.

We look forward to receiving your application by means of CV and motivation.

PostNL aims to be the favorite logistics company for everyone. Therefore everyone is welcome to join us irrespective of where you were born, what your beliefs are and who you love. We are simply looking for great talent.

